quran[13]{c,v,t,f}:
  18,98,"He said, “This is a mercy from my Lord; but when the promise of my Lord comes true, He will turn it into <span class=""h"">a flat surface<sup foot_note=""80505"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>. And the promise of my Lord has always been true.”"
  18,99,"And We left{1}them surging upon one another on that day, and the Trumpet was blown and We gathered them together.",footnotes:1:Frequently the Qur’an addresses the events of the hereafter in pasttense; this grammatical shift should be pondered by the reader.
  18,100,"And We displayed Hell to the deniers on that day in full display—"
  18,101,"those whose eyes were covered from My Reminder and were unable to hear."
  18,102,"Did those who have denied think that they could take My servants for masters apart from Me? Indeed, We have prepared Hell for the hospitality of the deniers."
  18,103,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “Shall We inform you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>of the biggest losers regarding deeds?"
  18,104,"Those whose efforts in the Earlier Life have gone astray, while they assume that they are doing well.”"
  18,105,"Those are the ones who denied the signs of their Lord and the meeting with Him, so their deeds were nullified, and on the Day of Resurrection We will consider them of no weight."
  18,106,"That is their repayment—Hell—on account of their denial and their taking My signs and My messengers in mockery."
  18,107,"Indeed, those who have attained faith and have done righteous deeds—the Gardens of Paradise have always been there for their hospitality,"
  18,108,"abiding therein, never seeking to leave it."
  18,109,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “If the sea were to become ink for the words of my Lord, the sea would run out before the words of my Lord ran out, even if We were to bring the like of it in replenishment.”"
  18,110,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “Indeed, I am only a human being like you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>. It is revealed to me that your god is One God, so whoever expects to meet his Lord, let him do righteous work and never associate anyone in the worship of his Lord.”"
